ber | HTTP status code indicating the category of the error.                     |\n| `message` | string | A human-readable description of what went wrong.                            |\n\n## Common status codes\n\n| Code | Meaning            | When it occurs                                         |\n|------|--------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|\n| 400  | Bad Request        | The request body or query parameters are malformed.    |\n| 401  | Unauthorized       | Missing or invalid authentication credentials.         |\n| 403  | Forbidden          | Authenticated but not permitted to access the resource.|\n| 404  | Not Found          | The requested resource does not exist.                 |\n| 429  | Too Many Requests  | Rate limit exceeded.                                   |\n| 500  | Internal Error     | An unexpected server-side failure.                     |\n\n## Example: handling errors in a client\n\n```python\nimport requests\n\nresp = requests.get(\"https://api.example.com/items/999\")\nif not resp.ok:\n    error = resp.json()\n    print(f\"[{error['code']}] {error['message']}\")\n```\n\nWhen an error occurs, always check both the `code` and `message` fields to\ndetermine the appropriate recovery action (retry, prompt for credentials,\nnotify the user, etc.).\n", "message": "docs(api/errors): expand error response reference with standard shape and examples"}, "id": "call_e9cc44f413d44919a6f7998d", "type": "tool_call"}, {"name": "create_or_update_file", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T16_R02_C03_A01", "branch": "main", "path": "docs/api/overview.md", "sha": "6aa119cd4321151bf9491e712018892169806baa", "content": "# API Overview\n\nThis section documents the demo API reference.\n\n## Error handling\n\nAll endpoints may return errors in a standard JSON format.\nSee [Error Responses](errors.md) for the full error response shape,\ncommon status codes, and usage examples.\n", "message": "docs(api/overview): expan